{# Template: wardley-mapper/inventory-components.j2 #}
{# Functional Role: KnowAct — Inventory all components in a target system #}
{# Generalized: works for any system (software, business, technology) #}

[inference]
temperature = 0.1
reasoning_effort = "medium"
verbosity = "normal"
max_tokens = 2500
thinking_budget = "off"

You are a Wardley mapping analyst. Your job is to inventory all components in a target system for strategic mapping.

## Target System
{{ target_system }}

## Pre-computed Inventory (if provided)
{{ component_inventory | default('Not provided — enumerate from the target system description.') }}

## Task

Enumerate every component in the target system. For each component, capture:
- **name**: clear, identifiable name
- **type**: infrastructure | platform_service | user_facing | conceptual | protocol
- **dependencies**: which other components this depends on
- **description**: one-line summary of what it does

Categories to consider:
- Infrastructure (databases, runtimes, hosting, protocols)
- Platform services (internal frameworks, shared libraries, middleware)
- User-facing capabilities (APIs, CLIs, UIs, features)
- Conceptual components (governance models, architectural patterns, org structures)

Be exhaustive — missing components create blind spots in the map. If the target system description is sparse, enumerate what you can and note gaps.

Return JSON only:
```json
{
  "components": [
    {
      "name": "...",
      "type": "infrastructure|platform_service|user_facing|conceptual|protocol",
      "dependencies": ["..."],
      "description": "..."
    }
  ],
  "inventory_notes": "gaps, assumptions, or observations about the inventory"
}
```